WEBVTT

00:15:58.740 --> 00:16:03.867
(Laughter)

00:16:03.891 --> 00:16:05.976
But there is a silver lining.

00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:07.874
The silver lining is, I think,

00:16:07.898 --> 00:16:11.976
kind of the reason that behavioral
economics is interesting and exciting.

00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:14.865
Are we Superman, or are we Homer Simpson?

00:16:15.286 --> 00:16:18.277
When it comes to building
the physical world,

00:16:18.301 --> 00:16:20.333
we kind of understand our limitations.

00:16:20.357 --> 00:16:21.528
We build steps.

00:16:21.552 --> 00:16:24.695
And we build these things
that not everybody can use, obviously.

00:16:24.719 --> 00:16:26.615
(Laughter)

00:16:26.639 --> 00:16:28.186
We understand our limitations,

00:16:28.210 --> 00:16:29.860
and we build around them.

00:16:29.884 --> 00:16:32.463
But for some reason, when it comes
to the mental world,